D'oh! I found the reason for the wrong values in Opera 9.5x and 9.6x. It seems to me that scrollWidth/scrollHeight also use invisible DOM elements for his calculation. If for example, the document contains a DOM element which is outside the viewport (top: -1000, left: -1000 and position: absolute), the scrollWidth/scrollHeight returns the size with the not visible element.

I would prefer to revert the change from rev. 19140, due to using the viewport is wrong if a native application is used. It is like Sebastian sad in commit #4, always using the viewport is wrong if scroll bars appear. Perhaps offsetHeight/offsetWidth could solve the issue for the buggy browsers.
Oh, also Safari 3 and Safari 4 returns wrong values if scroll bars occur.
I opened a separate bug #2869 for this issue on Opera 9.5x and Opera 9.6x

The issue on Opera 9.5x and Opera 9.6x couldn't be fixed, see bug2869.
